Package com.atakmap.comms

Class CotDispatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.atakmap.comms.CotDispatcher
  • public class CotDispatcher
extends java.lang.Object
    Dispatches CoT event Messages. The interface to this class is thread safe.

      • CotDispatcher

        public CotDispatcher()
        Create a default dispatcher that handles INTERNAL dispatched CoT events immediately on the calling thread.

      • CotDispatcher

        public CotDispatcher​(java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService internalDispatchExecutor)
        Create a dispatcher with an executor to handle internally routed CoT events. Passing null for the executor results in handling of INTERNAL CoT immediately on the calling thread.
        Parameters:
        internalDispatchExecutor - the executor to handle

      • CotDispatcher

        public CotDispatcher​(ParallelTrackExecutorService internalDispatchParallelTrackExecutor)
        Create a dispatcher with a "parallel track" executor to handle internally routed CoT events. Passing null for the executor results in handling of INTERNAL CoT immediately on the calling thread. The passed ParallelTrackExecutorService will be used such that each UID is guaranteed to be handled serially.
        Parameters:
        internalDispatchParallelTrackExecutor - the instance of ParallelTrackExecutorService or null

    • Method Detail

      • getSharedConcurrentInternalDispatchExecutor

        public static java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService getSharedConcurrentInternalDispatchExecutor()
        Get the Application-wide shared ExecutorService tuned for handling INTERNAL dispatched CoT efficiently and concurrently. The executor service is guaranteed to be a first-in, first executed, however, simultaneous updates are possible and must be accounted for in internal CoT handling.
        Returns:
        the shared ExecutorService

      • getSharedConcurrentInternalDispatchTrackExecutor

        public static ParallelTrackExecutorService getSharedConcurrentInternalDispatchTrackExecutor()
        Get the Application-wide shared ParallelTrackExecutorService tuned for handling INTERNAL CoT efficiently and concurrently. This ParallelTrackExecutorService differs from the getSharedConcurrentInternalDispatchExecutor ExecutorService in that it guarantees CoT Events with the same UID are processed serially.
        Returns:
        the shared ParallelTrackExecutorService

      • dispatch

        public final void dispatch​(CotEvent event)
        Used to dispatch a CotEvent with no additional directives passed in as a bundle. This method uses the dispatch flags set on the CoTDispatcher. If you want to pass in additional directives such as the "from" field, please use dispatch(CotEvent, Bundle)
        Parameters:
        event - the cot event to dispatch

      • dispatch

        public void dispatch​(CotEvent event,
                     android.os.Bundle data)
        Used to dispatch a CotEvent with no additional directions passed in as a bundle. This method uses the dispatch flags set on the CoTDispatcher.

        Note: If the bundle contains the "from" field and it is "internal" or is missing, the data is assumed to be internally generated and may trigger different code paths.

        Parameters:
        event - the cot event to dispatch

      • dispatch

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> dispatch​(CotEvent event,
                                                 android.os.Bundle data,
                                                 com.atakmap.commoncommo.CoTSendMethod sendMethod)
        Returns the contacts which are unknown, known to no longer be reachable, or who do not match the provided CoTSendMethod. Will always return an empty list for data Bundles that contain connect strings and no contacts, broadcasts (no contacts specified), or for internal-only dispatches since no actual remote contacts are involved.

        Data may contain a list of destination contacts "toUIDs" is a list of UIDs "toConnectStrings" is a list of stringified NetConnectString
